The paper discusses the history and analysis of attacks on industrial control systems, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the automation and data acquisition aspects of these systems, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the security implications of increased interconnectivity, which falls under the category of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the different types of attacks and their points of entry, which falls under the category of system and information security (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses targeted attack campaigns against industrial enterprises, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
